
üìÇ Default Linux Log Directory

/var/log     *** Stores system, application, security, kernel & service logs ***

üìç Common Log File Paths
/var/log/messages          *** General system logs ***
/var/log/secure            *** Authentication & security logs ***
/var/log/cron              *** Cron job logs ***
/var/log/dnf.log           *** Package installation logs ***
/var/log/boot.log          *** System boot logs ***
/var/log/dmesg             *** Kernel hardware detection logs ***
/var/log/audit/audit.log   *** SELinux & audit logs ***
/var/log/<appname>/        *** Custom application logs ***

üìÑ Basic Log Viewing Commands
cat file.log                  *** Print entire log ***
less file.log                 *** Scrollable log viewer ***
head -n 50 file.log           *** Show first 50 lines ***
tail file.log                 *** Show last 10 lines ***
tail -n 100 file.log          *** Show last 100 lines ***


üîç Searching Logs
grep "ERROR" file.log                     *** Search for keyword ***
grep -i failed /var/log/secure            *** Case-insensitive search ***
grep -r "timeout" /var/log                *** Recursive directory search ***
grep -E "ERROR|WARN" app.log              *** Regex multi-match ***
grep -v INFO app.log                      *** Exclude matching lines ***


üì° Real-Time Log Monitoring
tail -f file.log                          *** Live log streaming ***
tail -Fn50 file.log                       *** Follow after rotation ***
watch -n 2 tail file.log                  *** Refresh logs every 2 sec ***


üß© Journalctl (systemd logging)
journalctl                                *** Show all journal logs ***
journalctl -u sshd                        *** Logs for specific service ***
journalctl -u nginx -f                    *** Live follow service logs ***
journalctl --since "10 min ago"           *** Time-based filtering ***
journalctl -u NetworkManager --since "today"
journalctl -k							**** Kernel-level link drops are logged here***
grep -i network /var/log/messages
journalctl -u NetworkManager --since "2025-12-14 00:00:00" --until "2025-12-14 23:59:59"
journalctl -u NetworkManager --since "Dec 14"
journalctl -xe                            *** Show recent system errors ***
journalctl -k                             *** Kernel journal messages ***


üñ• Kernel, Boot & Hardware Logs
dmesg                                     *** Kernel ring buffer logs ***
dmesg -T | grep usb                       *** Hardware event timestamping ***
journalctl -b                             *** Current boot logs ***
journalctl -b -1                          *** Previous boot logs ***


üîê SELinux & Audit Logs
grep AVC /var/log/audit/audit.log         *** Check SELinux denials ***
ausearch -m AVC                           *** Query audit DB for violations ***
aureport -a                               *** Summarize access violations ***
sealert -a /var/log/audit/audit.log       *** Human-readable SELinux report ***
tail -f /var/log/audit/audit.log          *** Live audit event monitoring ***


üßë‚Äçüíª Authentication & Login History
last                                      *** Successful logins ***
lastb                                     *** Failed login attempts ***
last -a                                   *** Include source IP ***
faillog -u root                           *** Failed login count for user ***


üß∞ Rsyslog Management
systemctl status rsyslog                  *** Check rsyslog health ***
systemctl restart rsyslog                 *** Restart logging service ***
systemctl enable rsyslog                  *** Start at boot ***
logger "test message"                     *** Send test syslog entry ***
grep -i error /etc/rsyslog.conf           *** Check config issues ***


üß† Crash, OOM & Core Dumps
journalctl -xe | grep -i killed           *** Detect OOM kills ***
dmesg | grep -i oom                       *** Kernel Out-Of-Memory logs ***
coredumpctl list                          *** List core dumps ***
coredumpctl info <PID>                    *** View crash metadata ***


üî• Networking & Firewall Logs
journalctl -u firewalld                   *** Firewall activity ***
grep "DENIED" /var/log/firewalld          *** Blocked connections ***
tcpdump -nn -i eth0                       *** Live packet capture ***


üóú Compressed Log Access
zcat file.log.gz                          *** View compressed logs ***
zgrep ERROR file.log.gz                   *** Search compressed logs ***
zless file.log.gz                         *** Scroll compressed logs ***


üíæ Log Size, Disk & Rotation
du -sh /var/log            	               *** Total log size ***
du -sh /var/log/*                         *** Per-file size ***
df -h                                     *** Disk usage ***
logrotate -d /etc/logrotate.conf          *** Debug rotation ***
logrotate -f /etc/logrotate.conf          *** Force rotate ***

üßπ Journal Storage Maintenance
journalctl --disk-usage                   *** Show journal size ***
journalctl --vacuum-size=500M             *** Shrink journal ***
journalctl --vacuum-time=10d              *** Delete logs older than 10 days ***
journalctl --list-boots                   *** Boot history ***

üïµÔ∏è Advanced Log Filtering
grep -Ril "panic" /var/log                *** Find critical failures ***
awk '/ERROR/ {print $0}' app.log          *** Extract error lines ***
sort app.log | uniq -c | sort -nr         *** Count repeated log entries ***
grep -A3 -B2 "ERROR" file.log             *** Show context lines ***


üì¢ Real-Time Production Monitoring Combo
tail -f /var/log/messages | grep -Ei "error|fail|critical|panic"
*** Live alerting without monitoring tools ***


‚úÖ Standard Troubleshooting Workflow
systemctl status <service>
journalctl -u <service> -xe
grep -i error /var/log/messages
tail -f /var/log/<app>/<app>.log
grep AVC /var/log/audit/audit.log
df -h
du -sh /var/log/*








